<P>Again, those numbers were from old (3+ years) parsing logs and are rough estimates that have been debated even then.&nbsp; They are meant as only a sort of guide to give you an idea where you stand.</P>
<P>I will be the first to say they are not exact, but they are close enough for you to guage where you stand and to also re-iterate that while you can con the same message (dubious for example) you can be worlds apart where you stand on a mobs "dubious" list.&nbsp; While you won't get a merchant to sell to you at any "dubious" point, you may get a quest giver to acknowledge you if you are High dubious as opposed to low dubious.</P>
				
